Added explicit code pattern for protecting dashboard routes in Astro with requireAuth(). The requireAuth() function checks authentication status, and if the user is not authenticated, it issues an HTTP 302 redirect to the login page while preserving the originally requested URL for seamless post-login navigation. Relevant implementation:
```typescript
// From src/pages/dashboard/index.astro
const authRedirect = await requireAuth({
  cookies: Astro.cookies,
  redirect: Astro.redirect,
  request: Astro.request,
})

// From src/lib/auth.ts
export async function requireAuth({ cookies, redirect, request }) {
  const user = await getCurrentUser(cookies)
  if (!user) {
    const loginUrl = new URL(authConfig.redirects.authRequired, request.url)
    loginUrl.searchParams.set('redirect', request.url)
    return redirect(loginUrl.toString()) // <-- This creates the 302
  }
  return null
}
```
