Test assertions and business logic for the mental-llama evidence extraction system now comprehensively validate that each evidence item is an object, its text fields are strings and non-empty after trimming, and that non-object items or those lacking valid 'text' are skipped with logged details. Confidence scores are clamped to the 0-1 range for robustness:
