WandB MCP server configuration: The correct configuration for WandB MCP server in Cursor is to use "uvx" command with "wandb-mcp-server", not an HTTP endpoint. The configuration should be:
```json
"wandb": {
  "command": "uvx",
  "args": ["wandb-mcp-server"],
  "env": {
    "WANDB_API_KEY": "your-api-key"
  }
}
```
The endpoint https://mcp.withwandb.com/mcp returns 404 and is incorrect. The WandB MCP server is a command-based server that runs via uvx (UV's package runner), similar to how other MCP servers use npx. The API key must be set in the env section of the configuration.
